      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">52.216-30</ph> Time-and-Materials/Labor-Hour
Proposal Requirements-Non-Commercial Item Acquisition Without Adequate
Price Competition.</title>
      <conbody outputclass="provision" class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <p id="d3250e8" class="- topic/p ">As prescribed
in <ph outputclass="ClauseProvisionXREF" class="- topic/ph ">
               <xref href="FAR-i1103674.dita#i1103674"
                     base="i1103674"
                     outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                     class="- topic/xref ">16.601</xref>(f)(2)</ph>, insert
the following provision:</p>
         <p id="d3250e15"
            rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020"
            outputclass="Ctr_SmCaps"
            class="- topic/p "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-022?>Time-and-Materials/Labor-Hour Proposal
Requirements-Non-Commercial Item Acquisition Without Adequate Price
Competition (Aug 2020)<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 52.216-18 by—
a. Revising the date of the clause;?></p>
         <ol id="d3223e25" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3250e21" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph> The
Government contemplates award of a Time-and-Materials or Labor-Hour
type of contract resulting from this solicitation.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3250e26" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> The offeror
must specify separate fixed hourly rates in its offer that include
wages, overhead, general and administrative expenses, and profit
for each category of labor to be performed by-</p>
               <ol id="d3223e44" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d3250e32" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph> The offeror;</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d3250e37" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph> Each subcontractor;
and</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d3250e42" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph> Each division,
subsidiary, or affiliate of the offeror under a common control.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3250e47" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-022?>A delivery order or task
order is considered “issued” when—<?FM MARKER [Why] b. Revising paragraph (c); and?></ph>
               </p>
               <ol id="d3223e83" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d3250e56" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">If sent by mail (includes
transmittal by U.S. mail or private delivery service), the Government
deposits the order in the mail;</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d3250e62" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">If sent by fax, the Government
transmits the order to the Contractor's fax number; or</ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d3250e68">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">If sent electronically,
the Government either—</ph>
                     </p>
                     <ol class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d3250e75">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">Posts a copy of the delivery
order or task order to a Government document access system, and
notice is sent to the Contractor; or</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p class="- topic/p " id="d3250e81">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                              <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph ">Distributes the delivery
order or task order via email to the Contractor's email address.</ph>
                           </p>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d3250e87" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2020-07 August 3, 2020" class="- topic/ph "><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-022?>Orders may be issued by methods
other than those enumerated in this clause only if authorized in
the contract.<?FM MARKER [Why] c. Adding paragraph (d).?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
         <p outputclass="Endofprovision" class="- topic/p ">(End of provision)</p>
